od woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud Erdingham was born about 1260, in Aston, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of Henry Erdington. She had at least 1 son with Hugh Del Or Atte Holt."},"et":{"about 1260–":"umbes 1260–Surnud","1260–Female":"1260–Surnud","1260–1322":"1260–1322","1275–1347":"1275–1347","–Male":"Surnud","about 1260":"umbes 1260","1347":"1347","1322":"1322","Abt 1275":"umbes 1275","1275":"1275","1260":"1260","of Aston, Warwickshire, England":"Aston, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Newton, Cheshire, , England":"Newton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1260–":"noin 1260–Kuollut","1260–Female":"1260–Kuollut","1260–1322":"1260–1322","1275–1347":"1275–1347","–Male":"Kuollut","about 1260":"noin 1260","1347":"1347","1322":"1322","Abt 1275":"noin 1275","1275":"1275","1260":"1260","of Aston, Warwickshire, England":"Aston, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Newton, Cheshire, , England":"Newton, Cheshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"about 1260–":"environ 1260–Décédée","1260–Female":"1260–Décédée","1260–1322":"1260–1322","1275–1347":"1275–1347","–Male":"Décédé","about 1260":"environ 1260","1347":"1347","1322":"1322","Abt 1275":"environ 1275","1275":"1275","1260":"1260","of Aston, Warwickshire, England":"Aston, Warwickshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Newton, Cheshire, , England":"Newton, Cheshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Maud Erdingham est née environ 1260, à Aston, Warwickshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fille de Henry Erdington. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Hugh Del Or Atte Holt."},"de":{"about 1260–":"um 1260–Verstorben","1260–Female":"1260–Verstorben","1260–1322":"1260–1322","1275–1347":"12